This paper proposes a novel approach for differentially-private data release that leverages the Diaconis-Freedman-Meckes effect and random orthonormal projection. The paper presents multiple algorithms for a range of machine learning applications, including both unsupervised and supervised learning. The paper also rigorously proves the privacy guarantees of the proposed algorithms. Given the focus on machine learning and privacy, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Other likely sub-categories include cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.IT (Information Theory), and cs.DB (Databases).
